## Summary
Add GitHub Actions release workflow that builds the substrate CLI binary for both Linux and Windows, and uploads/publishes them on version tags.

## Context
The project needs a CI pipeline to produce release binaries for the substrate CLI (from the driver-cli package) so users can download pre-built executables for Linux and Windows without building from source.

## Changes
- Added .github/workflows/release-binary.yml - a new workflow file
- Fixed pre-existing formatting issues in crates/dispatch-bridge/src/lib.rs (cargo fmt)

### Workflow Details
- Triggers: v* tag pushes and workflow_dispatch (manual run)
- Build matrix: ubuntu-latest and windows-latest
- Steps: checkout, dtolnay/rust-toolchain@stable, cargo build --release -p driver-cli, upload artifact with OS-qualified name
- Release job: On v* tags only, downloads all matrix artifacts and attaches them to a GitHub Release via softprops/action-gh-release@v2 with auto-generated release notes

## Local Checks Run
The following local quality checks passed:
- cargo fmt --all -- --check - formatting verified clean
- YAML syntax validated via Python yaml.safe_load

## Testing
1. Trigger manually via GitHub UI (workflow_dispatch) - binaries should upload as artifacts
2. Push a v* tag - workflow should additionally create a Release with binaries attached
